titles.title: Air and Health Quality Empowerment Zone Designation Act of 2008
Air and Health Quality Empowerment Zone Designation Act of 2008

An original bill to address the health and economic development impacts of nonattainment of federally mandated air quality standards in the San Joaquin Valley, California, by designating air quality empowerment zones.

calendar.text: Committee on Environment and Public Works ordered to be reported an original measure.

action.text: Committee on Environment and Public Works. Original measure reported to Senate by Senator Boxer. With written report No. 110-500. Minority views filed.

calendar.text: Placed on Senate Legislative Calendar under General Orders. Calendar No. 1078.
